organic_results.title: The impact of Sesame Street on readiness
organic_results.snippet: This study investigated the effects of the first season of Sesame Street on readiness in kindergarten children. Metropolitan Readiness Test (MRT) scores of children from one school district, who had attended kindergarten in the two years prior to the first broadcast season, were compared with the scores of children who had attended kindergarten in 1970, the year of the first season of Sesame Street.
